title: Division Officer V-4/V-3 USS Enterprise CVN-65 "BIG E"
description: The flight deck of an aircraft carrier is one of the most dynamic and dangerous environments in the Navy. This is especially true for those that operate the catapults that launch tactical aircraft costing $100 million dollars each into the air and stop them by use of the arresting gear once the mission is complete. * Learning to become a fully qualified Catapult Officer takes 6 months; completed all training in less than 90 days.  Personally executed 5,000 launch evolutions without a single mishap.  Trained 5 Catapult/Arresting Gear Officers on the ship as well as leading a 120 (direct report)man division that not only operated all facets of the equipment but maintained it as well.  Courage of conviction and strong moral character fostered high morale, espirit de corps, and a total winning attitude in his division even though Enterprise executed two of the most arduous Persian Gulf deployments in its history. Outside of normal duties, also qualified Command Duty Officer Underway. V-4 Department: Responsible for over 2.7 million gallons of fuel on a daily basis. Inadvertent fuel spills at-sea are harmful to the envionment. Through constant training and strict adherence to procedures, this department had zero fuel spills over a two year period despite operating with the confines of a 50 year old ship. Set the record for all of Naval Aviation of getting 4 aircraft launched.
